+  lines.push("");
+  lines.push("The strongest supported patterns were treatment-by-biomarker relationships. Pembrolizumab was most favorable in tumors with higher PD-L1 TPS and TMB-high status, but STK11 mutation was adverse and reduced pembrolizumab-associated benefit. Sotorasib showed a strong KRAS G12C-specific benefit, olaparib showed a strong BRCA2-specific benefit, and osimertinib showed a strong EGFR-specific benefit. A pooled matched-targeted-therapy analysis across EGFR, KRAS G12C, and BRCA2-positive patients supported the same overall conclusion: biomarker-matched therapy was associated with materially longer PFS. Clinical severity, metastatic burden, inflammation, low albumin, high LDH, weight loss, squamous histology, current smoking, and several comorbidities were adverse prognostic signals.");
